: K.N. Satheesh has been removed as Director of Higher Secondary Education. The new appointee is Rural Development Commissioner K.V. Mohan Kumar.Mr. Satheesh had been in the eye of the storm over the transfer of higher secondary teachers in the State. The teachers had alleged anomalies and violation of norms in the transfer. The government had set up a four-member committee to look into the issue and the teachers had approached the Kerala Administrative Tribunal, too.However, the official version for the appointment of Mr. Mohan Kumar is that Mr. Satheesh was overloaded, with duties including that of executive officer of the Sree Padmanabhaswamy temple. â€” Staff Reporter